## API Proxy - Forward API calls to backend
/api/*  https://urban-nile.onrender.com/api/:splat 200!

## SPA Routing - Serve React app for all other paths
/*      /index.html                   200

# Explanation in comments:
# - /api/* preserves your backend proxy from netlify.toml
# - /* catch-all serves index.html for ALL frontend routes
# - React Router then handles routing client-side:
#   - Matches defined routes (/products, /login, /admin/*, etc.)
#   - Shows your NotFoundPage for invalid paths
# - Deploy: netlify.toml already builds to frontend/dist
# - _redirects will be copied to dist/_redirects automatically
# - Test: npm run build & check dist/_redirects exists
